{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who has shown remorse by partially reimbursing the stolen funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, a 10-year term as suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the amount stolen ($25,000) and the defendant's lack of prior record. A custodial sentence of 6 months is sufficient to serve as a deterrent and punishment while allowing for the possibility of continuing restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
